# Scheduling Algorithms (Condensed)

## When to Use
- OS process/thread schedulers, HPC/cloud task allocation, workflow DAGs, real-time embedded, container orchestration

## Fundamental OS Scheduling
- **FCFS**: O(1), simple, convoy effect
- **SJF/SRTF**: optimal avg waiting, needs burst prediction (exponential averaging), starvation
- **Round Robin**: O(1), time quantum (80% bursts < q), time-sharing
- **Priority + Aging**: prevents starvation
- **MLQ**: fixed queues (system/interactive/batch)
- **MLFQ**: dynamic promotion/demotion based on behavior, adapts I/O vs CPU-bound

## Parallel & Distributed
- **HEFT**: O(n²m), DAG on heterogeneous, upward rank + insertion scheduling
- **Min-Min**: O(n²m), favors short jobs, good load balance
- **Max-Min**: O(n²m), reduces makespan, poor balance
- **Suffrage**: max(second_best - best), balanced

## Metaheuristics
- **GA**: population → selection → crossover (OX, PMX) → mutation (swap, insert) → elitism
- **PSO**: particles + velocities, w/inertia + c1/c2 cognitive/social
- **VNS**: shake(solution, k) → local_search → if improved, reset k=1
- **ACO**: pheromone trails, ants construct solutions, evaporation + reinforcement
- **SA**: temperature cooling, accept worse with exp(-delta/T)

## Hybrid
- **GA-VNS**: GA global + VNS local refinement
- **ACO-GA**: ACO init population + GA explore + pheromone feedback
- **Memetic**: GA with local search every generation

## ML-Based Scheduling
- **RL (DQN/PPO/A3C)**: state=[loads, queue, time], action=assign, reward=-makespan
- **NN Predictors**: LSTM/Transformer predict runtime for HEFT input
- **GNN**: task graph → embeddings → policy network for DAG scheduling
- **NAS**: auto-design RL policy architectures

## Real-Time Scheduling
- **EDF**: dynamic priority, nearest deadline, utilization ≤ 1, optimal uniprocessor
- **RM/RMS**: static priority, shorter period = higher priority, utilization ≤ n(2^(1/n)-1) ≈ 0.693
- **DM**: priority by relative deadline (not period)
- **Multiprocessor**: Partitioned (bin-packing + EDF/RM), Global, Semi-partitioned

## Cloud & Container
- **K8s**: Predicates → Priorities → Bind; extensible via scheduler framework plugins
- **Borg**: Cell/Job/Task, feasibility + scoring, gang scheduling, preemption
- **YARN**: FIFO / Capacity / Fair Scheduler
- **Mesos**: Two-level (resource offers → framework acceptance)

## Workflow & DAG
- **CPM**: forward/backward pass, critical path = zero slack
- **List Scheduling**: priority order + assign to min finish time machine
- **Data Placement**: co-location, replication, staging

## Energy-Aware
- **DVFS**: Power ∝ V²f, trade freq for deadline
- **E-HEFT**: HEFT + energy constraint, scale freq on critical path
- **Thermal**: balance temperature across processors

## Metrics
| Metric | Goal |
|--------|------|
| Makespan | Minimize |
| Flow Time | Minimize |
| Tardiness | Minimize |
| Load Balance | Minimize std |
| Speedup | Maximize |
| Energy | Minimize |
| SLA Violations | Minimize |

## Key Complexity Summary
| Algorithm | Complexity |
|-----------|------------|
| FCFS/RR/MLFQ | O(1) |
| SJF | O(n log n) |
| EDF | O(log n) |
| HEFT/Min-Min/Max-Min | O(n²m) |
| GA | O(G·N·n) |
| PSO | O(I·N·n) |

